President Biden and Secretary-General Guterres of the United Nations met at the Intercontinental New York Barclay in New York City. President Biden expressed his gratitude for the Secretary-General's leadership during the pandemic and other global crises. He emphasized the importance of the partnership between the United States and the U.N., particularly in addressing challenges like COVID-19 and climate change. Both leaders reaffirmed their commitment to the principles of human freedom and dignity. President Biden mentioned the ambition of the United Nations in delivering prosperity, peace, and security through international cooperation. Secretary-General Guterres praised the United States' commitment to the U.N. and multilateralism and expressed a desire to deepen cooperation. The leaders discussed their shared values and concerns, including the well-being of vulnerable populations impacted by COVID-19, climate change, and other challenges. President Biden expressed optimism about the potential for positive change.